entries.femaleVariant: You look just as you did when I found you in the rubbish. Get up.
Takemura? What're you doin' here?
[Sit] What're you doin' here?
[Sit] Blunt, as usual.
Takemura. Blunt as usual.
They say you demanded someone tell you the truth.
It is an awful place... It is no wonder you are losing your mind.
Come all the way here to take me home?
They asked me to speak with you.
What'd you want to talk about?
Your beloved boss is back.
What exactly are you up to now?
Who was it asked you to talk to me?
What're you gonna do now? Still aim to protect Saburo's ass?
I have been transferred to Japan. I will fly from here to Takamatsu.
Why?
New times, new duties. But we say far too much about me.
Fine, so what is it you got to tell me?
I am sorry to say it is not good.
Who asked you? Who wanted you to talk to me? Hanako?
And what did they say?
I will be blunt – the surgery did not help.
You will be dead before winter.
But they've got experts, the best specialists...
Sorry, don't believe you.
Fuck.
How... How is that possible? Arasaka's got the best and brightest.
entries.maleVariant: How... How's that possible? Arasaka's got the best and brightest.

entries.femaleVariant: Sorry, don't believe you.
You wished to know the truth. There it is.
I... I really thought it'd all work out, end better than well.
Fuck.
Still got options?
A few months, that's all I got, right?
You promised Arasaka would fix me.
Dead in a few months – that's me, huh?
You will feel better at first, but then the illness will grow fierce, attack in full force.
Your final weeks you will spend in bed.
Said Arasaka would fix me if I helped you – you promised.
I believed truly they could.
Said you had powerful friends. Where're those friends now?
I did not come with empty hands. We must speak about your options.
Hanako Arasaka promised to save my life.
It is the reason she sent me here – to discuss the alternative.
What're you talkin' about? Trusted you all once already. You let me down.
You may join the "Secure Your Soul" program. Hanako Arasaka has agreed to it.
You will leave your body. Arasaka will store your engram in Mikoshi until a way is found to transfer it to a new body.
Store? Can't I get a new body right off?
With technology as it is now, this is impossible.
Seemed pretty damn possible for Saburo Arasaka.
He returned in his son's body. Tissue compatibility made things easier.
Don't wanna land in Mikoshi.
Arasaka just wants another soul in its collection.
Sorry, not buyin' it. Arasaka's out to lock me up.
You overstate your importance. To the Arasakas, I fear you are nobody – were nobody.
With this offer, Hanako Arasaka rewards you generously for your service. There is not, as you say, "more to the story."
There will be a contract to protect you. Sign it, and you will live.
Saw Saburo Arasaka's back. In Yorinobu's body.
Yes. Justice has been done.
So – got your revenge? Feel satisfied?
I believe Hanako Arasaka chose the best solution.
Whole family's fucked up.
Saburo Arasaka should've stayed dead.
Feel bad for Yorinobu Arasaka.
Whole family's all kinds of fucked up. You know that.
Please watch what you say.
Sister kills brother to plant her murdered dad in the brother's corpse? Straight-to-feeder flick right there.
They are diferrent from you and me. We do not have the right to judge them.
Saburo shoulda stayed dead.
Many wish him dead, but he will survive them all.
Y'know, the Arasakas belong in some sad old tragedy. Some Shakespeare-level shit there.
Yorinobu 'specially.
You regret his fate?
Wanted out of his dad's shadow, whatever the cost. Died at the hand of his worst nightmare.
You must accept the truth, then listen to what I say. There are options.
They have kept you here in this cell? For days? It is barbaric.
[Sit on bed]
[Take contract]
It is written here that you relinquish all rights, but do not worry. The law is simply behind the times – an engram is not legally a person.
So I get to be corporate property first?
Like many braindance stars and politicians, from what I know. The program is a success, there have been no complaints.
And if I say no?
This is not a prison. You will take your things and return to Night City.
Hey. What's your name?
Hajime.
Hajime, lemme ask you somethin'. What would you say to a person who walked right into their greatest foe's jail to save their life?
Hm. I would say, "All right. But do not forget the way home."
[Stand] See you around?
[Sign contract]
[Take things and return to Earth]
Were I you, I would sign. But the choice is yours. Think it through carefully.
[Take cube]
Arasaka keeps its word, always.
Don't wanna die.
A good choice.
The engram station is ready for you. We should not wait for your condition to worsen.
[Surrender to Arasaka]
Made my decision.
Goin' back to Earth, goin' home.
You will die there.
[Show middle finger]
[Return to Earth]
Gonna see each other again?
I believe we will.
So… see you.
You're all right, Takemura, I like you. Thanks for comin' all the way up here to help.
What is that?
[Stand] Goodbye, Takemura.
("A thing of beauty will never fade away.")
("I see your eyes, I know you see me, you're like a ghost how you're everywhere.")
I have come to speak with you.
Sorry, guess I'll never understand what you see in the guy.
You did not spend your life at his side and-- well... I did not come here to talk about the Arasakas.
She has forgotten you already. They called from here, from the clinic.
They said someone should talk with you. Someone you know.
No, no – the operation was a success, and that is why. But the changes the chip made were too great – even for the corporate neurosurgeons.
This is fuckin' Arasaka! They should figure somethin' out!
Fuck.
Please, feel no anger. I wish to speak about an alternative.
Nope, doesn't sound good to me at all. I agree to this, and they'll do whatever they want with me.
entries.maleVariant: Nope, doesn't sound good at all to me. I agree to this, and they'll do whatever they want with me.

entries.femaleVariant: Visit me in Kagawa – I will show you what is real food.
But one thing you never understood and never will.
Got no idea how sweet it is to be free.
You speak out of bitterness. Please reconsider.
No. This here's goodbye. But I'm not gonna forget you, what we did together.
Goodbye, V.
Yet your phenotype, thanks to the chip, is unique. Arasaka cannot provide a suitable body at this time.
[Take bag]
Rise, V, please – let us talk.
V-san?
Please, look.
Any thoughts?
You need not delay. There is nothing for you here any longer.
